Class Commands

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class Commands
extends javax.swing.JPanel
    This class provides and implements all controls to communicate with a PROSAC host. Each control provide a unique command that can be sent to PROSAC.
    Author:
    Bruno MARTINS, Gustavo CIOTTO PINTON
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • Commands

        public Commands()

    • Method Detail

      • disableAll

        public void disableAll()
        Disable all push buttons.

      • setCyclingEnabled

        public void setCyclingEnabled()
        Sets the interface to enable only ABORT_CYCLE command. It is called when a CYCLE_ENABLE was sent.

      • setCyclingDone

        public void setCyclingDone()
        Sets all buttons enabled as soon as the cycling curve was completed.

      • setRampSending

        public void setRampSending()
        Disables all buttons except SEND_BLOCK (0xC9) command button. It is called after the user chooses INIT_RAMP (0xC8).

      • setRampSent

        public void setRampSent()
        A ramp curve was successfully sent to PROSAC, thus all operations can be enabled, except ABORT_CYCLE and ABORT_RAMP.

      • setRampingEnabled

        public void setRampingEnabled()
        Enables only ABORT_RAMP. It is called after a ENABLE_RAMP or ENABLE_CYCLIC_RAMP commands are sent.

      • setRampingDone

        public void setRampingDone()
        A ramp has been completed, therefore all commands can be enabled.

      • setNormal

        public void setNormal()
        Normal state corresponds to all buttons enabled, except the ones that abort cycling and ramping operations.
